02bd18e2-a49d-43c8-bfbc-fd3c530fde52.072fd26e-f321-4f63-be98-1ee3739a22c8.prompt=Enter a value for keystorePassword 02bd18e2-a49d-43c8-bfbc-fd3c530fde52.0fc887b7-9422-4990-ab63-8c82803826cd.prompt=Enter a value for keystore 02bd18e2-a49d-43c8-bfbc-fd3c530fde52.15096325-5237-4a9b-b4fe-8a43f6945d5e.prompt=User Identifier 02bd18e2-a49d-43c8-bfbc-fd3c530fde52.332f1fa2-2749-48a2-a77b-c1c468d6dc00.description=
This workflow returns the user details for given user.

Inputs-
userId –  CSA User Id
userIdentifier  - User Identifier id
authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
socketTimeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for the data to be retrieved. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A socketTimeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
followRedirects - If true, the GET command automatically follows redirects. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true
proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: true
keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client authentication is not to be used.
keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.

Outputs-
userName – User name for the provided user id
document  – returned XML document from API

Create a change request ticket.

Inputs\:
host - The DNS name or IP Address of your Service Manager host.
port - The port to connect to your Service Manager host on.
protocol - The protocol to connect to your Service Manager host with. Either HTTP or HTTPS.
username - The username for the Service Manager host. The user should have only a sysadmin profile (falcon, on a default SM installation).
password - The password for the Service Manager user.
smVersion - Version of Service Manager. If the given value is empty or contains only spaces the default version 'sm700' will be used.
actualCost - Actual cost.
approvalStatus - Change approval status.
assignee - Assignee of ticket.
assignmentGroup - Primary assignment group. This is a valid input starting with SM version 7.10 and is required.
assets - Assets (sometimes interchangeable with Configuration Item).
briefDescription - Brief description (one-line); corresponds to "Title" in SM interface.
category - The category of the change.
configItem - Configuration item (sometimes interchangeable with Configuration Item).
contact - Contact for the ticket.
coordinator - The coordinator of the change.
description - Ticket description.
estimateDescription - Cost estimate description.
estimatePrice - Cost estimate.
initialImpact - Initial impact (eg. 1,2,3,4).
journalUpdates - Update history (new-line delimited).
location - the location for the change, starting with SM version 7.10.  
misc1 - mapped to "Change Tester" in SM interface.
misc2 - mapped to "Testing results (pass ot fail)" in SM interface.
misc3 - mapped to "Brief Description" in SM interface.
open - Open the ticket?
plannedEndDate - Planned end date/time.
plannedStartDate - Planned start date/time.
priority - Ticket priority (eg. 1,2,3).
reason - Reason for action / change.
requestedBy - Ticket requester. A full name should be provided in the form LAST NAME, FIRST NAME (eg. FALCON, JENNIFER). Corresponds to "Initiated by" in SM interface.
requestedEndDate - Requested end date by initiator. This is a valid input starting with SM version 7.10 and is required.
service - Affected service. This is a valid input starting with  SM  version 7.10 and is required.
severity - Severity (sometimes called User Priority) (eg. 1,2,3,4). 
subCategory - Subcategory / area.
scheduledOutageStart - Scheduled outage start date/time.
scheduledOutageEnd - Scheduled outage end date/time.
releaseType - The release type for this change. This should be provided if and only if the category of the change is Release Management, and its valid values are Hardware Release or Software Release; otherwise, it should be left empty. 
department - The department of the assignee (should only be assigned a value when creating a new change having 'RFC - Advanced' as category in SM 7.00 or SM 7.01).
riskAssessment - The risk assessment (should only be assigned a value when creating a new change having 'RFC - Advanced' as category in SM 7.00 or SM 7.01).

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
smMessage - Service Manager request brief message
smMessages - Service manager request additional messages
smReturnCode - Service Manager request's return code
smStatus - Service Manager request return status
id - Ticket ID

Note\:
The values for the inputs should be the ones permitted by Service Manager. The allowed values can be found in the corresponding underlying database. 

The value for the date inputs should be provided in one of the following forms\: mm/dd/yyyy hh\:mm\:ss GMT+/-hh\:mm or mm/dd/yyyy GMT+/-hh\:mm, otherwise an unparsable date error is obtained.

This workflow initiates a request approval by using SM 9.30 as defined external approval system.It creates a Change request ticket in Service Manager. The same can be viewed by loging into SM client using user having approval privileges. e.g account \: Change.Approver

Inputs\:

CSA_CONTEXT_ID 	\: CSA Context Id
CSA_PROCESS_ID 	\: CSA Process Instance Id
SVC_COMPONENT_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
RSC_PROVIDER_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL \: This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is                                                         [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE 	\: This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
RSC_POOL_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
SVC_INSTANCE_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
PRN_COMPONENT_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
REQ_ORG_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
REQ_USER_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
USR_ORG_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
RSC_BINDING_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]
APPROVAL_PROCESS_ID	\: This token will resolve to the external approval process Id that was created during initiating approval request. Default value for this token is                                                                                [TOKEN\:APPROVAL_PROCESS_ID]
APPROVAL_CONTEXT_ID	\: This token will resolve to the external approval context Id that was created during initiating approval request.Default value for this token is                                                                                 [TOKEN\:APPROVAL_CONTEXT_ID]
USER_CONTEXT_ID	\: This token will resolve to the user context Id that was created during initiating approval request.Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:USER_CONTEXT_ID]
ORGANIZATION_ID	\: This token will resolve to the organization Id that was created during initiating approval request.Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:ORGANIZATION_ID]
CATALOG_ID	\: This token will resolve to the organization Id that was created during initiating approval request.Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:CATALOG_ID]

These tokens with the default values are resolved by CSA when the flow is invoked.

Responses\:
success 		\: Workflow completed successfully.
failure 		\: Something went wrong.
